text: the Jolly Green Giant has been an
ambassador for processed vegetable since
1928 he's brought us canned frozen and
now pouched what's in it a sit on the

Green Giant veggie blend ins which the
creator's say is one way to tackle our
vegetable shortfall we are eating on
average barely half as many servings of
vegetables as we should get selling
vegetables is quite profitable so some
nifty experimentation is going on in the
produce aisle shopping carts tricked out
with signs to nudges into buying more
produce breeding for cuteness like baby
red peppers and lots of prep work to
make them easier to buy and eat all this
is aimed making them appear on our plate
more often but the Green Giant is
ambling the other direction making
vegetables disappear into other foods
for people who routinely avoid them the
potential pitfalls with these blend is
the price of convenience and some
dubious cross-marketing among the
recipes on the box is a pouch of spinach
added to the Giants sister brand Betty
Crocker's fudge brownie mix which would
deliver barely a teaspoon of vegetables
to each brownie for such a big price
that's a pretty small dent in the
vegetable deficit
